    Genetic link`
    < a type of (§) intercast link
    - function
        - declares a waybit to be a member of a waybit population
        - structures the waybit population by nominal lines of genetic descent
        - indicates approval of ancestral waybit content
            ( Votorola-style transitive vote flow ('delegate cascade') in a recombinant text
            - each genetic link is formally a vote
                - whereby the caster (vote caster = waycaster) formally approves (votes for)
                  the content of the genetic parent and (by transitive vote flow) its ancestors
            - here the vote caster is every waycaster for whom that genetic link is on way
                ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/way#on_way
                - warrant
                    - being on way
                        - the waybit is used
                        - and usage implies approval
                    - to avoid forcing the formation of direct links merely to express the approvals
                      that are already implied by the indirect link
    [ general to all forms
        * referring waybit
            - all genetic links specify a referring waybit
            - is a waybit local to the declaring waycast
        * *link* attribute
            < cog:link, namespace data:,wayscript.cog
            ( cf: http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/script/doc.task § jointers: the *link* attribute
            - most genetic links specify a *link* attribute
            - the *link* attribute is a URL in form
            - function (*as* a genetic link)
                - effective only if the subjoining waybit is:
                    - a waybit
                    - a member of the same population as the *referring waybit*
                        - otherwise it is a link across a population boundary
                            - which is instead a phylogenetic link
                            - declaring the referent population to be a parent population
                - declares
                    - the subjoining waybit to be a genetic parent
                    - the referring waybit to be its genetic child
    [ particular forms
        § intercast joint
            - every intercast joint is also a genetic link
            - function (*as* a genetic link)
                - locates the *referring waybit* as that replica of the subjoining waybit
                  that results from resolving the referential joint
                - declares the referring waybit to be a member of the subjoining waybit's population
                    - and a clonal child of the subjoining waybit
                - asserts that the subjoining waybit is a member of a population
                    - if the subjoining waybit declares no population itself
                        - nor implies any by its encoding
                        - then it is hereby declared a member (the founding member) of population L
                        - where L is the normalized value of the *link* attribute
            - meaning: a diachronic genealogical relation
                - distinct from any synchronic, merely formal (and so meaningless)
                  genealogical relation of nesting in which the joined elements may be involved
                    ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/script/doc.task § Nesting of waybit elements
        § *patch* element, q.v.
    - a nominal relation
        - the declared relation is nominal
            - as opposed to ontic
            - it does not imply actual generative text flows and editorial influences
        - rather it implies an *intended* genetics in accord with the practical
          (e.g. collaborative) purpose of the (§) waybit population
    - cycles
        - formally possible in lines of descent (*link* attributes)
            ( exactly as in Votorola
        - meaning of cycles will vary with the particular function of the link under consideration
        - effect will vary with the practical context, and may be blocked in some contexts

