    *patch* element`
    - function
        - declares a variant waybit
            - one whose content differs from other members of the waybit population
        - declares a (§) genetic link
        - replaces the content of the genetic parent (if any) wherever in the way definition it occurs
            ( no matter how remote from the waycast, how deep (indirect) the linkage
            - with that of the variant
        - effective iff:
             & the parent (referent of *cog:link*)
                - and/or the content (referent of *href*)
                - is on way
                    ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/way#on_way
                - so proper to the waycaster
                ( else it is weird
             & the waycast declares no other variant waybit of the same population
    - form
          | <patch [cog:link='PARENT-URL'] [cog:population='POPULATION-ID'] [href='CONTENT-URL']>
          |     [CONTENT]
          |     </patch>
        - genetic link attributes
            - at least one of these must be declared
            * *link* attribute
                ( § genetic link § *link* attribute
            * *population* attribute
                < cog:population, namespace data:,wayscript.cog
                - identifies the variant waybit's population
                - default value: normalized PARENT-URL
        - content, either of:
            * inline content
                - defines a new waybit
                - declares it to be the *referring waybit*
                    ( § genetic link § referring waybit
            * *href* attribute
                < no namespace
                - an intracast, relative reference in form
                    ( https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986#section-4.2
                    - thus proper to the waycaster
                    ( else it is weird
                - locates the *referring waybit*
                    ( § genetic link § referring waybit
    - placement
        - in an on-way document
            ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/lex/way#on_way
            - which is the root way declaration document
                ( http://reluk.ca/project/wayic/cast/root#root_way_declaration_document
                - or any other document that contains an on-way element
        - thereby easily detectable by processors

