    Waybit population`
    < a type of intercast network
    - a group of waybits interrelated by nominal lines of descent
    - purpose
        - competitive and collaborative way definition among waycasters
            ( akin to recombinant text in textbender and Votorola
        - efficient editorial search among variant waybits
        - formation of way consensus
            ( akin to a Votorola poll
    - network link form: genetic link
    - identifier: a URI in form
        - only because it happens to be referenced by the *link* attribute of genetic links
            ( otherwise it could be a free form string
    [ typical practice
        + surface variation
            - pasting the variant content directly in line, no referential jointing
            = write this
                - situation
                    - you already have waybit
                    - you want to declare it to be a variant waybit
                - method
                    - an empty *patch* element
                        - typically placed within the waybit
                        - with an *href* attribute referencing the waybit
                        - and possibly other attributes
                            ( as per § subsurface variation
        + shallow variation
            - subsurface variation (§) of a directly linked waybit
            - form, either of
                | generalized subsurface variant
                    ( § subsurface variation
                | surface variant
                    = write this
                        - replacing the referential jointer with a surface variant
                            ( § surface variation
                        - it ends up formed as such
        + subsurface variation
            ( generalized form
            - changing the content of a linked waybit
                - no matter how deep in the waycaster network (indirect) its linkage
                - by making a variant of it
            - the linked waybit
                - is an intercast subjoining waybit
                - is on way
                - is the waybit you want to change
                - will become the nominal genetic parent of your newly made variant
            - make an empty *patch* element
                - preferably near to the intercast jointer
                - the one that gives access to the content you wish to change
            * declaring the genetic parentage
                - add attribute cog:link='PARENT-URL' to reference the chosen genetic parent
                    ( § *patch* element
                    - namely the waybit whose content you want to change
            * declaring the population
                - skip this if the parent is a member of no waybit population
                    - instead letting the population default to PARENT-URL
                - add attribute cog:population='POPULATION-ID' to identify the parent's population
                    - it is declared in the genetic parent
                        - or inferrable from it
                        ( typically a tool will tell you the value
            * declaring the variant content
                - copy the (§) genetic content of the parent
                    - typically a tool will properly filter the content for you
                - paste it
                    - either in the *patch* element
                    - or elsewhere, referenced by adding the attribute href='CONTENT-URL'
                - edit the content to change it
        + delegation to another waycaster
            - the other waycaster has declared a variant of your waybit, which you like
            - you no longer want to maintain this waybit yourself
            - replace it with an intercast joint to the variant
              and let the other waycaster maintain it

